WEBVTT

00:02.936 --> 00:05.173
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:28.262 --> 00:29.430
Psst.

00:29.463 --> 00:31.365
I need to talk to you
about the pants.

00:31.399 --> 00:33.301
Well, come closer, then.
No, thanks.

00:33.334 --> 00:35.269
I don't want to get contaminated
by your buffoonery.

00:35.303 --> 00:37.338
What's wrong with
my pants?

00:37.371 --> 00:39.907
Dude, it looks like a gnome is
carrying you on his shoulders.

00:39.940 --> 00:42.510
Look who's talking.
Have you seen your sandals?

00:42.543 --> 00:44.245
You look like you're about
to walk on water.

00:44.278 --> 00:45.713
Well, you look like
you prolapsed

00:45.746 --> 00:46.880
your whole
digestive system!

00:46.914 --> 00:48.416
You look like
a Visigoth tourist.

00:48.449 --> 00:50.918
You look like you're wearing
the back end of a horse costume!

00:50.951 --> 00:52.553
Yeah, well, you look
like this!

00:52.586 --> 00:54.455
[ Humming ] Huh?

00:54.488 --> 00:55.456
Pbht.

00:55.489 --> 00:58.226
Hey, dude,
only one guy can judge me.

00:59.493 --> 01:00.361
Leslie!

01:00.394 --> 01:01.762
If there was
a fashion police,

01:01.795 --> 01:03.164
he'd be
the town's sheriff,

01:03.197 --> 01:04.865
only more fabulous.

01:04.898 --> 01:07.835
Are you pointing at that broken
accordion on a pile of trash?

01:07.868 --> 01:09.937
Sorry. It's hard to tell
what's what

01:09.970 --> 01:11.639
since
his high-fashion phase.

01:11.672 --> 01:13.141
[ Upbeat music plays ]

01:13.174 --> 01:15.109
♪ Uh, head shot, body shot

01:15.143 --> 01:17.178
♪ Paparazzi, twist and bop

01:17.211 --> 01:19.079
♪ Head shot, body shot

01:19.113 --> 01:21.149
♪ Looking nasty,
turn and smile ♪

01:21.182 --> 01:23.016
♪ Catwalk beauty,
catwalk beauty ♪

01:23.050 --> 01:25.186
♪ Beauty, fashion

01:25.219 --> 01:27.221
Yeah, fair enough.
Where is he, though?

01:27.255 --> 01:29.857
Come to think of it,
I haven't seen him in weeks.

01:29.890 --> 01:31.525
Wait, what is that?!

01:31.559 --> 01:33.261
Hmm. Petals.

01:33.294 --> 01:34.628
[ Gasps ]
It's a clue.

01:34.662 --> 01:36.029
What do you mean?

01:36.063 --> 01:37.231
Think about it --
what has petals? Flowers.

01:37.265 --> 01:38.766
What is made of flour?
Bread.

01:38.799 --> 01:40.100
Who eats bread?
Everyone...

01:40.134 --> 01:41.669
apart from people
who can't eat gluten.

01:41.702 --> 01:43.937
Who doesn't eat gluten?
People on a made-up diet.

01:43.971 --> 01:46.940
What kind of people are usually
on fad diets? Drama queens.

01:46.974 --> 01:48.842
Who are usually drama queens?
Actors.

01:48.876 --> 01:50.144
And what do actors do
in real life?

01:50.178 --> 01:51.845
They work as waiters
in the food industry.

01:51.879 --> 01:53.947
And where do they lie about not
working in the food industry?

01:53.981 --> 01:55.849
In their dressing rooms.

01:56.417 --> 01:57.918
Huh!
You were right!
[ Sobbing ]

01:57.951 --> 01:59.553
You said that like
it's a surprise.

01:59.587 --> 02:01.255
Hey, dude,
could you help us decide on

02:01.289 --> 02:02.456
which of us looks worse?

02:02.490 --> 02:04.525
[ Growls ]
[ Both scream ]

02:04.558 --> 02:05.459
Question answered.

02:05.493 --> 02:07.795
Dude, what in
the ever-loving what

02:07.828 --> 02:09.297
happened to your face?!

02:09.330 --> 02:12.700
[ Sighs ]
My beauty...it's fading.

02:12.733 --> 02:15.303
It's not that bad.
I mean, if I just squint --

02:15.336 --> 02:16.704
Wait, no.
That's still pretty bad.

02:16.737 --> 02:17.938
But if I just --

02:17.971 --> 02:19.673
No, that's -- that's
not great, either.

02:19.707 --> 02:20.741
But if I just...

02:20.774 --> 02:21.875
See, that's better!

02:21.909 --> 02:23.477
Look, don't worry.

02:23.511 --> 02:27.215
True beauty is found on the
inside -- your personality.

02:27.248 --> 02:29.483
Good-looking people
don't need a personality!

02:29.517 --> 02:31.619
Personalities were invented
by ugly people

02:31.652 --> 02:34.121
to make up for what
they lack on the outside!

02:34.154 --> 02:37.124
But you can't spell "beautiful"
without "B-U."

02:37.157 --> 02:39.593
And you can't spell "hideous"
without "hide",

02:39.627 --> 02:41.495
which is what I'm doing!

02:41.529 --> 02:42.896
[ Sobbing ]

02:42.930 --> 02:45.766
Don't worry. We'll help you
get pretty again.

02:45.799 --> 02:46.767
Thank you.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.135
Hmpf!

02:48.168 --> 02:50.103
Sorry.
It's just...

02:50.137 --> 02:51.138
your face.

02:51.171 --> 02:52.240
[ Inhales ]

02:52.273 --> 02:53.707
Let's start
with accessories.

02:53.741 --> 02:56.477
Hopefully it will distract
from the...everything.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.979
Is that why you carry Darwin
everywhere you go?

02:59.012 --> 03:00.614
[ Snaps fingers ]
Mm-mm!

03:00.648 --> 03:02.883
You know, when you're pretty
and you say something mean,

03:02.916 --> 03:04.518
people think you're sassy.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.019
But with a face like that,
people think you're Sasquatch.

03:06.053 --> 03:07.721
Now, come on,
accessorize.

03:07.755 --> 03:11.325
♪♪

03:11.359 --> 03:13.694
Ugh. It looks like the ugly tree
and the Christmas tree

03:13.727 --> 03:15.663
had a baby and let him dress
himself for school.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.898
So, yeah, definitely
an improvement.

03:17.931 --> 03:19.367
[ Gagging ]

03:19.400 --> 03:21.001
Look,
he's speechless!

03:21.034 --> 03:23.203
Wow! He fainted
from happiness!

03:23.237 --> 03:25.306
And now he's having spasms
of satisfaction!

03:25.339 --> 03:26.607
[ Gagging continues ]
Uh...

03:26.640 --> 03:28.442
Leslie,
is something wrong?

03:28.476 --> 03:30.944
[ Strained ] I can't
photosynthesize.

03:30.978 --> 03:34.348
Is that when you store all your
photos in a cloud or the...

03:34.382 --> 03:36.684
I can't breathe!
[ Gasping ]

03:36.717 --> 03:38.018
Quick, give him CPR!

03:38.051 --> 03:39.487
O-Oh, okay.
Oh, oh.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.855
I can't.
He's so ugly.

03:41.889 --> 03:43.223
[ Breathing frantically ]

03:43.257 --> 03:45.459
[ Gagging ]

03:45.493 --> 03:46.126
Mmph!

03:46.159 --> 03:48.095
[ Inhaling, exhaling ]

03:48.128 --> 03:49.029
[ Both gasp ]

03:49.062 --> 03:50.097
[ Coughing ] Ugh!

03:50.130 --> 03:51.799
Who told you
[inhales sharply]

03:51.832 --> 03:52.700
to stop!

03:52.733 --> 03:53.901
No, no, no.
No!

03:53.934 --> 03:55.503
Gumball: Okay,
so you know about

03:55.536 --> 03:56.937
the cheerleader effect, right?

03:56.970 --> 03:59.039
What's that?
It's an optical
mind trick.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.775
When girls hang out in groups,
they look prettier.

04:01.809 --> 04:03.110
ALL: Go, Elmore, go!

04:03.143 --> 04:05.479
[ Upbeat techno plays ]

04:08.816 --> 04:10.217
Come on, let's try it.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.084
Hey, Penny!

04:11.118 --> 04:11.952
Yeah?

04:11.985 --> 04:13.654
How do we look?

04:13.687 --> 04:16.457
Ah. You're going for
the cheerleader effect, right?

04:16.490 --> 04:19.059
Yes.
Sorry, but for boys,
it's the opposite.

04:19.092 --> 04:20.494
We call it
the frat-guy effect.

04:20.528 --> 04:22.696
Makes you guys look like
medieval pillaging creeps.

04:22.730 --> 04:25.098
But would you still love me
if I looked like this?

04:25.132 --> 04:27.635
Yeah, you'd still be
the shining sun of my life.

04:27.668 --> 04:28.536
Aww!

04:28.569 --> 04:30.471
Impossible to live
without...

04:30.504 --> 04:33.474
but it'd really hurt my eyes
to look at you directly.

04:33.507 --> 04:35.909
What about now?
Mwah. Much better.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.378
What about my face?

04:37.411 --> 04:39.146
Well, it's like, you know
when a movie comes out

04:39.179 --> 04:41.749
and you're just like, "The
sequel can't possibly be worse,"

04:41.782 --> 04:42.750
then it is?

04:42.783 --> 04:44.818
Well, it's like
the 10th movie.

04:44.852 --> 04:47.921
[ Sobbing, sniffles ]

04:47.955 --> 04:48.789
Huah!
Aah!

04:48.822 --> 04:49.790
How is that possible?

04:49.823 --> 04:51.759
You look even uglier than
a second ago!

04:51.792 --> 04:54.061
You're right.
His condition's deteriorating.

04:54.094 --> 04:55.996
Maybe you can try and...
own it?

04:56.029 --> 04:57.197
What do you mean?

04:57.230 --> 04:58.666
You know,
like our Grandpa Louie.

04:58.699 --> 05:00.934
He never lets his age get in
the way of stripping off

05:00.968 --> 05:02.436
for his
life-drawing classes.

05:02.470 --> 05:04.204
And he doesn't care when
the teacher body-shames him

05:04.237 --> 05:05.739
by saying, "There's
no need to get naked

05:05.773 --> 05:07.074
when you're the one
doing the drawing."

05:07.107 --> 05:08.175
He's right.

05:08.208 --> 05:09.977
If you've got it,
flaunt it.

05:10.010 --> 05:11.144
Hmm.

05:11.178 --> 05:12.446
[ Siren wailing ]

05:12.480 --> 05:14.515
You may have flaunted it
too much.

05:14.548 --> 05:17.250
Oh, my gosh!
My eyes! My eyes!

05:19.453 --> 05:21.054
Hmm. What's that
you're using?

05:21.088 --> 05:22.222
A moisturizer.

05:22.255 --> 05:23.624
It might help lift

05:23.657 --> 05:26.093
the asymmetrical
drooping side of your face.

05:26.894 --> 05:29.029
I guess we'll just have to wait
for the opposite side

05:29.062 --> 05:30.063
to collapse instead.

05:30.097 --> 05:31.298
Hmm.
What's in it?

05:31.331 --> 05:32.633
Uh...aloe vera?

05:32.666 --> 05:35.302
Aloe vera?!
Are you insane?!

05:35.335 --> 05:37.438
What?! Why?!
It's made of cactus!

05:37.471 --> 05:39.740
That's like rubbing the blended
remains of your cousins

05:39.773 --> 05:40.908
on your face!

05:40.941 --> 05:42.976
None of that stuff
is made for use on plants!

05:43.010 --> 05:44.144
Yet.

05:44.177 --> 05:46.780
Gentlemen, it's time
for science.

05:46.814 --> 05:47.981
Man: Science.

05:48.015 --> 05:50.918
[ New Age music plays ]

05:55.789 --> 05:57.024
[ Sizzle! ]

05:57.057 --> 05:58.426
Eureka!

05:58.459 --> 05:59.927
What?
Nothing.

05:59.960 --> 06:02.062
Normally when people do all that
stuff and shout "eureka",

06:02.095 --> 06:03.397
they get the answer.

06:03.431 --> 06:06.667
I just thought that was
the formula for science.

06:06.700 --> 06:07.334
[ Munch! ]

06:07.367 --> 06:08.702
What are you doing?!

06:08.736 --> 06:11.138
Eating this gardening book
to absorb its knowledge.

06:11.171 --> 06:12.139
Agh! Give me that!

06:12.172 --> 06:13.641
You give me that!

06:13.674 --> 06:15.643
Wait, what were you
gonna do with it?
Read it!

06:15.676 --> 06:18.378
Yeah, well, that's exactly what
I was gonna do, so pbht!

06:18.412 --> 06:19.713
Reading, reading,
reading, reading.

06:19.747 --> 06:21.915
[ Gasps ] Got it!
You need more sun.

06:25.719 --> 06:26.987
Hmm.

06:29.289 --> 06:31.391
Hmmmmm.

06:33.026 --> 06:34.094
Whuuuuh!

06:34.127 --> 06:35.496
[ Panting ]

06:35.529 --> 06:38.499
Wait, maybe the fire will
improve his face.

06:39.700 --> 06:40.934
Hmm, hmm.

06:40.968 --> 06:43.537
Oh! It says here
you might need more water.

06:43.571 --> 06:45.372
Ooh!

06:46.440 --> 06:47.808
Maybe a little more?

06:48.676 --> 06:50.944
♪♪

06:50.978 --> 06:52.179
[ Muffled scream ]

06:52.212 --> 06:53.514
How do I look?

06:53.547 --> 06:55.816
Like a bullfrog that got
a face transplant

06:55.849 --> 06:57.485
from
a grilled cheese sandwich?

06:57.518 --> 06:59.920
Oh. It says here that the
problem might be caused

06:59.953 --> 07:01.489
by a parasite.

07:02.956 --> 07:04.257
[ Coughing ]

07:04.291 --> 07:06.694
Wait!
[ Coughing ]

07:09.497 --> 07:11.832
[ Gasps ]
I'm beautiful.

07:11.865 --> 07:12.900
Wait!

07:12.933 --> 07:15.068
I'm more beautiful
than I've ever been!

07:15.102 --> 07:19.072
Look at me, world,
and gag on my eleganza!

07:19.106 --> 07:21.174
[ Laughs ]

07:21.208 --> 07:22.910
[ Laughs weakly ]

07:24.144 --> 07:25.345
[ Burps ]

07:26.213 --> 07:27.481
[ Sighs ]

07:27.515 --> 07:29.683
It doesn't matter.
We still love you.

07:29.717 --> 07:32.352
I don't care if you -- Oh!
Nngh!

07:32.385 --> 07:34.555
I don't care about
the people who love me!

07:34.588 --> 07:36.223
I've already got their
validation!

07:36.256 --> 07:39.159
It's the people who don't
love me I need to impress!

07:39.192 --> 07:40.494
Wait a second.

07:40.528 --> 07:42.696
Dude, I've got it!
You're just wilting!

07:42.730 --> 07:44.765
It's completely normal!
Really?

07:44.798 --> 07:47.200
Yeah, and there's
a very simple solution.

07:47.234 --> 07:49.036
What is it?!
Ahh?

07:49.069 --> 07:50.938
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:50.971 --> 07:51.939
[ Screams ]

07:51.972 --> 07:53.006
Move!

07:53.040 --> 07:54.474
Leave me alone!

07:54.508 --> 07:57.177
Dude, take it easy!
It doesn't have to be an ordeal!

07:57.210 --> 08:00.180
Yeah, think about like a nice,
relaxing bit of gardening!

08:00.213 --> 08:03.617
[ Soft music plays ]
Hello, and welcome to
"Gardening Thyme."

08:05.152 --> 08:07.655
[ Birds chirping ]

08:07.688 --> 08:09.990
Today's episode is about
the seasonal decapitation

08:10.023 --> 08:11.124
of flowers.

08:11.158 --> 08:12.626
Or as we gardeners
call it

08:12.660 --> 08:14.427
[Inhales] dead-heading.

08:14.461 --> 08:17.898
You people are insane!

08:17.931 --> 08:19.800
Aah!

08:19.833 --> 08:21.769
[ Whimpering ]

08:26.974 --> 08:28.075
[ Screams ]

08:29.309 --> 08:31.244
[ Engine sputtering ]

08:31.278 --> 08:32.279
Come on, you stup--

08:32.312 --> 08:34.948
[ Both scream ]

08:34.982 --> 08:37.117
[ Muffled ] It won't start
unless it's in "park."

08:37.150 --> 08:38.586
Hmm?

08:38.619 --> 08:40.353
It won't start
unless it's in "park."

08:40.387 --> 08:41.221
Oh. Thanks.

08:41.254 --> 08:42.455
[ Engine starts ]

08:42.489 --> 08:43.624
[ Screams ]

08:43.657 --> 08:44.858
[ Tires squealing ]

08:44.892 --> 08:46.159
[ Crash! ]

08:46.193 --> 08:49.897
I'm not a monster!
I just look like one!

08:49.930 --> 08:51.064
[ Gasps ]

08:52.700 --> 08:55.535
You see, Darwin,
it is important to choose

08:55.569 --> 08:57.037
the right tools
for the job.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.205
Why not a chainsaw?

08:58.238 --> 08:59.707
[ Chuckles ]
Slow down there.

08:59.740 --> 09:01.041
We don't want to make
a mess.

09:01.074 --> 09:04.044
What we need is
a clean cut to the stem.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.979
[ Screams ]

09:08.616 --> 09:10.317
Help, help, help!

09:10.350 --> 09:12.820
Sir, please help!

09:12.853 --> 09:13.987
[ Growls ]

09:14.021 --> 09:15.255
[ Screams ]

09:15.288 --> 09:17.457
Please, please!

09:17.490 --> 09:18.959
[ Whirring ]

09:18.992 --> 09:20.393
[ Screams ]

09:22.329 --> 09:24.965
Ma'am, please help!
There are these kids who --

09:24.998 --> 09:25.833
[ Gasps ]

09:25.866 --> 09:26.967
[ Hissing ]

09:27.000 --> 09:28.869
Meh, meh, meh.

09:30.871 --> 09:32.205
[ Panting ]

09:32.239 --> 09:33.607
[ Gasps ]

09:33.641 --> 09:34.908
[ Screams ]

09:34.942 --> 09:36.409
[ Panting ]

09:37.410 --> 09:40.914
Please! Please!
Leave me alone!

09:40.948 --> 09:41.949
Ugh.

09:43.250 --> 09:44.517
What are these?

09:44.551 --> 09:45.385
[ Shing! ]

09:45.418 --> 09:46.920
[ Screams ]

09:49.790 --> 09:51.725
Make sure you don't waste
the flower heads

09:51.759 --> 09:53.426
and add them to
the compost heap.

09:53.460 --> 09:54.762
Very good point, Gumball.

09:54.795 --> 09:56.697
In time, their rotten remains
will be eaten

09:56.730 --> 09:58.198
and excreted by worms.

09:58.231 --> 10:01.001
The resulting matter can be used
to feed other plants.

10:01.034 --> 10:03.270
[ Screams ]

10:03.303 --> 10:05.072
[ Sobbing ]

10:05.105 --> 10:07.040
The police!
I need to call the police!

10:07.074 --> 10:07.841
[ Panting ]

10:07.875 --> 10:09.309
Argh!
No network?

10:09.342 --> 10:10.644
Come on, come on!

10:10.678 --> 10:11.679
[ Door creaks ]

10:11.712 --> 10:13.113
[ Gasps ]
They're coming.

10:13.146 --> 10:16.183
Gumball and Darwin:
Leslie, where are you?

10:16.216 --> 10:19.586
Leslie?

10:19.619 --> 10:20.587
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:20.620 --> 10:21.922
[ Screams ]

10:21.955 --> 10:23.523
Leslie, stop being such
a drama queen

10:23.556 --> 10:24.858
and listen to us
for a second.

10:24.892 --> 10:26.860
Since when is being
scared of decapitation

10:26.894 --> 10:28.228
considered overdramatic?!

10:28.261 --> 10:30.197
We're doing this for
your own good, man.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.900
Think about your face.
It will just continue rotting.

10:32.933 --> 10:35.736
Wait. So you're saying it's
better to leave a hot memory

10:35.769 --> 10:37.270
than cold compost.

10:37.304 --> 10:38.806
I agree. Do it.

10:38.839 --> 10:41.374
What? No, no.
Your head will regrow.

10:41.408 --> 10:43.476
Ah. All right, then.

10:43.510 --> 10:47.247
[ Screaming ]

10:47.280 --> 10:48.181
[ Plop! ]

10:48.215 --> 10:49.750
Ugh.

10:49.783 --> 10:51.952
And that concludes
our episode.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.554
And when will we see our pretty
new flower grow, Gumball?

10:54.587 --> 10:57.057
When spring comes back
in about six months.

10:57.090 --> 10:58.125
[ Shing! Shing! ]

10:58.158 --> 11:00.894
[ Both scream ]

11:02.395 --> 11:04.531
[ Theme music plays ]
